Prior to being drafted in the 2003 NBA Draft, LeBron’s future organization located along Lake Erie was down and out. However, once he stepped foot in Cleveland for his first NBA experience, things changed in the wins category for the Cavaliers right along with him. The Cavs saw a huge rise in success for years, reaching the playoffs multiple times, and even the NBA Finals once in 2007. However, when James left to take his talents to South Beach, the Wine and Gold fell right back down to the bottom of the barrel in the NBA. It wasn’t until the King returned home did the Cavaliers have significant playoff success again. James then left again for Los Angeles, and once again, Cleveland fell to mediocrity.


Code
cavs &lt;- nbastats |&gt; filter(Team == "Cleveland Cavaliers")
heat &lt;- nbastats |&gt; filter (Team == "Miami Heat")
lakers &lt;- nbastats |&gt; filter (Team == "Los Angeles Lakers")

ggplot() + 
  geom_line(data=nbastats, aes(x=as.numeric(Season), y=`W/L%`, group=Team), color="lightgrey") +
  geom_line(data=cavs, aes(x=as.numeric(Season), y=`W/L%`, group=1), color="#860038") +
  geom_line(data=heat, aes(x=as.numeric(Season), y=`W/L%`, group=1), color="#F9A01B") +
  geom_line(data=lakers, aes(x=as.numeric(Season), y=`W/L%`, group=1), color="#552583") +
  geom_rect(aes(xmin=2003, xmax=2009, ymin=0, ymax=1), fill="#BC945C", alpha=.2) + 
  geom_rect(aes(xmin=2014, xmax=2017, ymin=0, ymax=1), fill="#BC945C", alpha=.2) +
  geom_text(aes(x=2006, y=.9, label="LBJ's first Cavs run")) +
  geom_text(aes(x=2016, y=.95, label="LBJ's second Cavs run")) +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 1)) +
  labs(
    title = "LeBron Brought Winning During Cavaliers Tenures", 
    subtitle = "In the years that King James was with Cleveland, the team had immediate rises in success.",
    caption = "Source: Basketball Reference | By Jacob Schrantz",
    x = "Season",
    y = "Win/Loss %"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    plot.title = element_text(size = 20, face = "bold"),
    axis.title = element_text(size =10), 
    plot.subtitle = element_text(size=10), 
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
    plot.title.position = "plot"
    )







